<mixertitle>GAP&nbsp;3 Share Package "gliss" (GLISSANDO)</mixertitle>

<h3>
  GLISSANDO: Small Semigroups and Nearrings
</h3>
<p>
  Share package since release 3.4, about Apri 1997.<br />
  This package has not been transfered to GAP&nbsp;4, but the
  GAP&nbsp;4 package
  <a href="/Packages/sonata.html">SONATA</a> covers its functionality 
related to nearrings, and a library of small semigroups in GAP 4 is 
<a href="https://www.gap-system.org/Packages/smallsemi.html">Smallsemi</a>.
</p>

<h3>
  Author
</h3>
<p>
  <mixer person="Christof Noebauer" data="name"/>.
</p>

<h3>
  Implementation
</h3>
<p>
  <b>Language:</b> C <br />
  <b>Operating system:</b> Any <br />
  <b>Current version:</b> 1.0 (in the 3.4.4 distribution)
</p>

<h3>
  Description
</h3>
<p>
  GLISSANDO is a GAP&nbsp;3 package consisting of libraries of small
  semigoups (orders 1 - 5) and near-rings (orders 2 - 15) and functions for
  examining them.
</p>

